The paper focuses on clustering, which is a fundamental task in unsupervised learning, and proposes new optimization algorithms that can cope with large scale problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also suggests two new applications, unsupervised face identification and interactive multi-object segmentation by rough boundary delineation, which are related to Computer Vision (cs.CV), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
